3 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Contents of petition -- establishment of claim for compensation. (1)
4 A claimant may bring a civil action against the state or county of conviction in the district court in which the
5 conviction originated to seek the relief provided for in [section 6]. All claims of compensation are governed by
6 the Montana Rules of Civil Procedure. The claim must be:
7 (a) accompanied by a statement of facts explaining the basis of the claim, including if:
8 (i) the charge for which the claimant seeks compensation was dismissed;
9 (ii) the claimant was found not guilty at a retrial; or
10 (iii) only if either (1)(a)(i) or (1)(a)(ii) is not met, a proffer establishing actual innocence;
11 (b) written and verified by the claimant under penalty of perjury; and
12 (c) filed within a period of 3 years after the date of exoneration DISPOSITION.
13 (2) A claimant convicted, imprisoned, and released from custody before July 1, 2025, who intends
14 to bring an action under [sections 1 through 8] shall commence the action no later than July 1, 2028.
15 (3) All pleadings must be captioned as follows: "In the matter of the wrongful conviction of [name of
16 claimant]."
17 (4) (a) A claimant may receive a transition assistance grant of $5,000. The claimant shall verify by
18 affidavit filed with the department of corrections that the claimant satisfies the requirements set forth in
19 subsection (1), under penalty of perjury. Within 30 days of receiving the claimant's affidavit, the department of
20 corrections shall issue the grant funds to the claimant.
21 (b) If the claimant fails to file a claim within the time period described in this section, or if the claim
22 is denied by the district court, the claimant shall reimburse the state in the amount of $5,000 within 1 year
23 following receipt of the grant money.
24 (5) Nothing in [sections 1 through 8] permits a person who petitions a court for expungement of a
25 felony conviction for a crime that is now legal under Title 16, chapter 12, to seek compensation for a wrongful
26 conviction.
