11 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Offset provision. In the event the waiver or release provided under
12 [section 3(1)] is held invalid in whole or in part for any reason:
13 (1) if, at the time of an award of monetary damages or compensation under [section 6], the
14 claimant has also been awarded damages against the state, a political subdivision, or their officers, employees,
15 agents, or volunteers in a civil action related to the claimant’s same wrongful conviction or imprisonment,
16 including any settlement, the amount awarded under [section 6] must be reduced by the amount of damages or
17 compensation previously awarded; and
18 (2) if, after the time of an award of monetary damages or compensation under [section 6], the
19 claimant is awarded damages against the state, a political subdivision, or their officers, employees, agents, or
20 volunteers in a civil action related to the claimant’s same wrongful conviction or imprisonment, including any
21 settlement, the claimant shall reimburse to the state or a political subdivision of the state any amount awarded
22 under [section 6].
